\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {14}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Truncation sensitivity: anchored turns are invariant across all 5 CoT levels (Phase~A).} \emph  {Left:} Agreement heatmap for representative anchored (red rows) and exploring (green rows) turns --- each cell shows whether that truncation level produced the same answer as the 100\%~CoT level. Anchored turns are all-green; exploring turns have at least one red cell. \emph  {Right:} Histogram of unique answer count across 5 levels: anchored turns always produce exactly~1 unique answer; exploring turns produce~2 or more. The bimodal distribution validates the binary anchored/exploring classification.}}{26}{figure.14}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:truncsens}{{14}{26}{\textbf {Truncation sensitivity: anchored turns are invariant across all 5 CoT levels (Phase~A).} \emph {Left:} Agreement heatmap for representative anchored (red rows) and exploring (green rows) turns --- each cell shows whether that truncation level produced the same answer as the 100\%~CoT level. Anchored turns are all-green; exploring turns have at least one red cell. \emph {Right:} Histogram of unique answer count across 5 levels: anchored turns always produce exactly~1 unique answer; exploring turns produce~2 or more. The bimodal distribution validates the binary anchored/exploring classification}{figure.14}{}}
